    "long_instructions": "**The Scenario:**\r\n\r\nDenzel just got back from a sailing trip, and he’s inspired by the rising and falling waves of the sea. He wants his song to mimic that movement—growing louder and more intense, then fading back into calm.\r\n\r\n**Do This:**\r\n\r\n- Choose effects like **delays, volume changes, and filters** to create a smooth ebb and flow.\r\n- Gradually increase and decrease intensity — think of your remix as a series of musical waves.\r\n- Use **rests** and **sequencing** to stagger sounds so they don’t all peak at once.\r\n- Try **low, medium, and high settings** on your effects to control the shape and strength of your waves.\r\n- Listen and adjust: Does your song move like the ocean? If not, keep tweaking to make it feel more fluid.\r\n\r\n**Musical Suggestions:**\r\n\r\n- “Hallelujah” – Rosa Linn *(soft swells and emotional peaks that rise like tides)*\r\n- “Gravity” – Tinashe *(smooth, flowing structure you can build on)*\r\n- “In The Stars” – Benson Boone *(gentle but powerful builds with room to breathe)*\r\n\r\n**To pass this level, your remix must include at least 3 rising and falling moments using effects, rests, or volume to mimic the motion of waves.**",
    "display_name": "Ocean's Rhythm",
    "bubble_choice_description": "You're now a sound artist, and your challenge is to capture the motion of the ocean using sound!",
